# About #

This repository contains source code of Clover Core as well as it's integrations: Clover-for-Ant, Clover-for-Eclipse
and Clover-for-IDEA plugins. Sources are licensed under Apache 2.0 license.

# Documentation #

Atlassian Answers: http://answers.atlassian.com/tags/clover

User documentation: http://confluence.atlassian.com/display/CLOVER/Clover+Documentation+Home

Support KB: http://confluence.atlassian.com/display/CLOVERKB/Clover+Knowledge+Base+Home

Bug and feature tracker: https://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CLOV

Atlassian Support: https://support.atlassian.com/browse/CLV

Download page: http://www.atlassian.com/software/clover/download

Source code: https://bitbucket.org/atlassian/clover

See also:
  https://bitbucket.org/atlassian/grails-clover-plugin
  https://bitbucket.org/atlassian/maven-clover2-plugin
  https://bitbucket.org/atlassian/clover-examples


# Contributing #

In case you would like to contribute, please sign Atlassian Contributor License Agreement:

* [Corporate CLA](https://na2.docusign.net/Member/PowerFormSigning.aspx?PowerFormId=e1c17c66-ca4d-4aab-a953-2c231af4a20b)
* [Individual CLA](https://na2.docusign.net/Member/PowerFormSigning.aspx?PowerFormId=3f94fbdc-2fbe-46ac-b14c-5d152700ae5d)


Developer documentation:

* [Clover Development Hub|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/CLOVER/Clover+Development+Hub]

Note: Binary files have been removed from repository history, they are now being fetched from Maven repositories.
This repository can be used to build Clover 4.0 or higher. In case you need to build an older version, you will
have to download binaries and put in appropriate places, as required by build scripts.


